cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

The paper deals with object detection and localization in images using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves modifying the loss function of a fully convolutional network, which is a technique used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the method using different datasets, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The task of locating objects can also be related to robotics and autonomous systems (cs.RO). Finally, the paper mentions the evaluation of the method on datasets related to human faces and plant centers, which can be considered as multimedia (cs.MM).
